{
  "stem": "20616.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We were told that when we landed in France, our-- we would be divided into detachments.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And we would, while in France, would run towns and cities and so on as civil affairs.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And as soon as we crossed the border, we would become a military government.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And we were-- at the university, we had to do research on a landkreis in Germany.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And it was in such a detail that we knew exactly where everything was, where the police station was, where the government, who the governor was, and what his duties were, what the duty of this person was, and so on.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "The only thing is the army, being what it was, I think I was the only soldier in the United States who actually landed in that landkreis that we studied.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Everyone-- we also, not only that one, but we also had three landkreise, which were counties, and that we had to run later on.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "In France, we had to-- we followed the troops just as they were advancing.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "We were always right behind them, setting up the water, the utilities, some semblance of government.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And then we moved to the next town.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And later on, as the armies advanced, there were displaced persons.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "We had to run displaced person camps.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And we ran one of the biggest one, of, of all places in Trier, the town where my mother comes from.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "In fact, there was a big article written about that camp in I may still have it someplace-- and also in magazine.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And it was one of the largest camps.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "There were lots of experiences in that, in that camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "But I don't know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "It's going get a little bit too involved here, I think.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Hm?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I remember when President Roosevelt died.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
